title: John Gorka-Jacks Crows; excellent acoustic/folk/jazz EAC FLAC
description:
In 1991, Rolling Stone magazine called him "the preeminent male singer-songwriter of what has been dubbed the New Folk Movement." Although he never commercially lived up to these high expectations, artistically he surely did. He has a warm, nuanced and resonant baritone voice that just drips out of the speakers. Coupled with the excellent lyrics and melodies this makes great listening. 
You can see one of the tracks from this album below...

Backing musicians include Shawn Colvin, David Wilcox and The Turtle Island String Quartet, all accompanied by his rich guitar tones. 

Very highly recommended
